                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> At a court for the honour of <placeName key="place_106146">Reylegh</placeName>, held 27 Oct., <origDate notBefore="1365-01-25" notAfter="1366-01-24">39 Ed. III</origDate>, came
                  the <persName>prior of <orgName role="prior" key="org_105048">Horkislegh</orgName>
                        </persName> and produced many charters showing that the tenements which
                  the prior and convent of Horkislegh hold in <placeName key="place_106118">Horkislegh</placeName> of the aforesaid honour by
                  knights' service, and for which default in suit had been made, were given to the
                  prior and convent by <persName nymRef="Creffeld">
                           <forename>Henry</forename>
                        </persName> and
                  <persName>
                           <forename>Alan</forename> de <surname>Creffeld</surname>
                        </persName> in frankalmoigne, and the prior in
                  his own person made suit for the same. 
                  </p>
                  </msItem>
